On the first birthday of the United States Space Force, President Trump sends his best wishes to the men and women of the Space Force. He compares the Space Force's establishment to the historic achievement of landing on the moon and emphasizes the American spirit that drives exploration and innovation. The President commends the brave Americans who have joined the Space Force and recognizes their role in securing peace and protecting the nation through space exploration and commercialization. He celebrates the Space Force's contribution to extending the safety and security of the United States and expresses gratitude to all those who serve in uniform. The President concludes by invoking the Space Force's motto, "Always Above," and calling for continued blessings on the United States.